values ('itf-f-ch1-l1-s6', 'itf-f-ch1-l1', 'itf-f-ch1-l1-milestone', 6, 'Check the four computer categories', 'multiple_choice', 'assessment', 'Which summary correctly names and classifies the computer categories described in the lesson?', 'multiple_choice', '', null, '[{"id": "a", "text": "Desktop, laptop, tablet, and smartphone are the four types of general-purpose personal computers. Embedded computers, servers, and supercomputers are specific-purpose: embedded computers sit inside and control a larger machine and are often called control modules, servers handle many small client requests, and supercomputers handle one big request."}, {"id": "b", "text": "Desktop, laptop, server, and supercomputer are the four types of personal computers. Embedded computers are general-purpose, while personal computers are specific-purpose."}, {"id": "c", "text": "Desktop, laptop, tablet, and smartphone are specific-purpose computers. Servers handle one big request, while supercomputers handle many small client requests."}, {"id": "d", "text": "Embedded computers are personal computers found outside machines. Servers and supercomputers are both general-purpose computers because they perform every kind of task."}]'::jsonb, '{}'::jsonb, ARRAY['itf.computers.categories']::text[], 1, 'assessment', 'mcq')
