values ('itf-f-ch1-l2-s4', 'itf-f-ch1-l2', 'itf-f-ch1-l2-milestone', 4, 'Classify system parts', 'reflection', 'practice', 'Organize your answer into three groups. First classify each personal-computer device as input or output and name its signal form—sound, light, or pressure: microphone, keyboard, screen, mouse, camera, speaker, digitizer. Second classify the human parts skin, arms, eyes, legs, ears, and mouth as input or output. Third classify the elevator parts screen, door motor, cabin motor, cabin operating panel, and door infrared sensor as input or output. Explain the rule you used.', 'text', '', null, '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::jsonb, ARRAY['systems.input', 'systems.output', 'itf.signals.types']::text[], 1, 'reflection', null)
