values ('itf-f-ch1-l2-s6', 'itf-f-ch1-l2', 'itf-f-ch1-l2-milestone', 6, 'Check systems and signals', 'multiple_choice', 'assessment', 'Which summary is fully consistent with the lesson?', 'multiple_choice', '', null, '[{"id": "a", "text": "A system can be living or nonliving and has parts that work together to produce change. A signal is a message carried in physical form; sound and infrared light are signal forms. Input devices capture signals and actuators are output devices: for example, a microphone is sound input, a screen is light output, human skin is input, and an elevator door motor is output."}, {"id": "b", "text": "Only machines can be systems. Signals are messages without physical form. Input devices emit signals, and actuators are input devices."}, {"id": "c", "text": "A system cannot change input to output. Sound is a signal form, but infrared light is not. Actuators capture the user''s input."}, {"id": "d", "text": "A system is one part working alone. Input devices capture only light signals, and every output device must be a screen."}]'::jsonb, '{}'::jsonb, ARRAY['systems.input', 'systems.process', 'systems.output', 'itf.signals.types']::text[], 1, 'assessment', 'mcq')
