values ('itf-f-ch1-l4', 104, 'Memory', 'Use the saved-photo story to show why a computer needs both main memory and storage. Keep the distinctions concrete: main memory is limited and volatile, storage is larger and nonvolatile, and signals are copied rather than moved between them.', '', 'IT Frontiers', 'Beginner', 'itf-f-ch1', 4, 'published', 'guided', true, 'after_attempt', 'encouraging', 'guided', 'lower', '{"course_id": "itf-f", "course_version_id": "itf-f-v1", "lesson_type": "discussion"}'::jsonb)
