values ('itf-f-ch1-l4-s3', 'itf-f-ch1-l4', 'itf-f-ch1-l4-milestone', 3, 'Save, power off, and retrieve', 'discussion', 'teach', 'Signals in storage stay after a computer is powered off, while signals in main memory are lost. When Leena powers on her phone later and selects the photograph''s thumbnail, the stored signals are copied to main memory, processed, and sent as output to the screen, so she sees the photograph again. Signals transferred between main memory and storage are copied, not moved: summoning a signal from storage leaves the original safe in storage. Main memory is therefore volatile—it loses its signals without power—while storage is nonvolatile.', 'text', '', null, '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::jsonb, ARRAY['memory.storage']::text[], 1, 'explanation', null)
