values ('itf-f-ch1-l4-s4', 'itf-f-ch1-l4', 'itf-f-ch1-l4-milestone', 4, 'HDD and SSD storage', 'discussion', 'teach', 'Storage is performed by a drive. The two drive types are the hard disk drive (HDD) and the solid state drive (SSD), and both provide nonvolatile storage. An HDD uses magnetic rotating disks, while an SSD uses electronic microchips. Magnetic disks need more space and are heavier than microchips, so an HDD is larger and heavier, while an SSD is smaller and lighter. The SSD is based on electronic technology; the HDD is based on magnetic technology.', 'text', '', null, '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::jsonb, ARRAY['memory.storage']::text[], 1, 'explanation', null)
