values ('itf-f-ch1-l4-s6', 'itf-f-ch1-l4', 'itf-f-ch1-l4-milestone', 6, 'Check memory and drives', 'multiple_choice', 'assessment', 'Which summary is fully correct?', 'multiple_choice', '', null, '[{"id": "a", "text": "Memory holds signals, and main memory and storage are both parts of computer memory. Storage is larger and nonvolatile, preserves original signals because transfers are copies, and is performed by drives. HDDs use magnetic disks and are larger and heavier; SSDs use electronic microchips and are smaller and lighter."}, {"id": "b", "text": "Main memory is larger than storage and keeps its signals after power is off. Signals are moved out of storage, so no original remains. SSDs use magnetic disks."}, {"id": "c", "text": "Storage is volatile and is not part of computer memory. HDDs use electronic microchips and are smaller and lighter than SSDs."}, {"id": "d", "text": "Memory does not hold signals. Storage is performed by the processor, and turning off a computer empties both main memory and storage."}]'::jsonb, '{}'::jsonb, ARRAY['memory.storage']::text[], 1, 'assessment', 'mcq')
