values ('itf-f-ch2-l1-s2', 'itf-f-ch2-l1', 'itf-f-ch2-l1-milestone', 2, 'Clock rate', 'discussion', 'teach', 'One way to measure performance is to count how many input-output cycles a processor can execute in one second. Because the clock controls those cycles, its speed helps determine the processor''s speed. This speed is the clock rate, measured in Hertz (Hz). In Example 1.2, a clock that signals "Go" 8 times per second lets the processor execute 8 cycles per second, so its clock rate is 8 Hz. Modern processors execute billions of cycles per second. Giga means billion, so a 2 GHz processor executes 2 billion input-output cycles per second.', 'text', '', null, '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::jsonb, ARRAY['itf.hardware.performance']::text[], 1, 'explanation', null)
