values ('itf-f-ch2-l1-s4', 'itf-f-ch2-l1', 'itf-f-ch2-l1-milestone', 4, 'Compare core count fairly', 'discussion', 'teach', 'Another way to improve performance is to manufacture a CPU with more processors, called cores. In Example 1.4, Ahmed notices another laptop that looks exactly the same and also runs at 3 GHz, but one laptop has a single-core CPU and the other has a quad-core CPU. At the same clock rate, the quad-core CPU should be faster. Example 1.5 compares one, two, and four cores while keeping the rate at 2 GHz; more cores should be faster. Example 1.6 keeps two cores and compares 1, 2, and 3 GHz; the faster clock rate should be faster. A dual-core CPU is not necessarily exactly twice as fast as a single-core CPU, and a quad-core CPU is not necessarily exactly four times as fast.', 'text', '', null, '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::jsonb, ARRAY['itf.hardware.performance']::text[], 1, 'explanation', null)
