values ('itf-f-ch3-l3-s1', 'itf-f-ch3-l3', 'itf-f-ch3-l3-milestone', 1, 'A condition controls an action', 'discussion', 'intro', 'Instructions that indicate how to make a decision are called conditional instructions. The decision depends on the conditions present when the instruction is performed. Chen''s usual school instructions did not account for rain, so his parents added: if it is raining, then wear a raincoat and take an umbrella. Those actions happen only when the condition is met. If it is not raining, no rain action is taken and Chen moves on to get his school bag. In a flowchart, the decision is shown in a diamond-shaped box. Its Yes branch performs the rain actions and its No branch skips them; both paths then continue to the next instruction.', 'text', '', null, '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::jsonb, ARRAY['jargon.if', 'itf.logic.conditionals']::text[], 1, 'explanation', null)
