values ('itf-f-ch3-l3-s3', 'itf-f-ch3-l3', 'itf-f-ch3-l3-milestone', 3, 'BIOS decides from a device signal', 'discussion', 'teach', 'A BIOS device test first sends ''Are you OK?'' and waits for a reply. It cannot assume that every reply says ''I am OK.'' The conditional test asks whether the signal equals ''I am OK.'' On Yes, BIOS writes that the device is OK to memory and connects it. On No, BIOS writes that the device is not OK and prints an error saying it is not connected. A keyboard can fail this test by explicitly replying ''I am not OK,'' sending an unreadable signal, or not replying at all. In all three cases, the device is not OK, so the No path is followed.', 'text', '', null, '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::jsonb, ARRAY['jargon.if', 'itf.logic.conditionals']::text[], 1, 'explanation', null)
