values ('itf-f-ch3-l3-s5', 'itf-f-ch3-l3', 'itf-f-ch3-l3-milestone', 5, 'Complete two decision flowcharts', 'discussion', 'practice', 'Write the process steps and Yes/No branches for two decisions. For Lin, test whether it is raining: state what happens when it is raining and when it is not. For the elevator''s embedded computer, test whether something blocks the doorway: if the doorway is clear, close the doors; if it is blocked, wait and check again. State what happens for each branch and what happens if the blocking object never moves. Present each as an ordered instruction list or a text description of the matching flowchart.', 'text', '', null, '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::jsonb, ARRAY['jargon.if', 'itf.logic.conditionals']::text[], 1, 'practice', 'applied')
