values ('itf-f-ch3-l4-s1', 'itf-f-ch3-l4', 'itf-f-ch3-l4-milestone', 1, 'A loop repeats instructions', 'discussion', 'intro', 'Repeating instructions is sometimes needed to complete a task. A robot''s embedded computer needs a program for every task. MI7''s walking program lifts a foot, swings the leg forward, sets the foot down, and then switches legs. One pass makes only one step, so the program repeats from its first instruction. This creates a loop. Without a number of repetitions or a stopping condition, it is an infinite loop: MI7 keeps walking forever, and the processor is stuck doing that one task only.', 'text', '', null, '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::jsonb, ARRAY['jargon.loop', 'itf.logic.repetition']::text[], 1, 'explanation', null)
