values ('itf-f-ch3-l4-s2', 'itf-f-ch3-l4', 'itf-f-ch3-l4-milestone', 2, 'A stopping condition breaks the loop', 'discussion', 'teach', 'To avoid an infinite loop, the instructions need a stopping rule. One rule specifies the number of repetitions. The processor counts each repetition, and when the specified number is reached, it breaks the loop and ends the program. In MI7''s flowchart, the robot lifts, swings, sets down, and switches legs before a decision asks whether the repetition count has reached the limit. No returns to the first walking instruction; Yes breaks the loop. If MI7 must walk 14 steps, the condition uses 14 as that limit.', 'text', '', null, '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::jsonb, ARRAY['jargon.loop', 'itf.logic.repetition']::text[], 1, 'explanation', null)
