values ('itf-f-ch4-l1-s4', 'itf-f-ch4-l1', 'itf-f-ch4-l1-milestone', 4, 'Build a list and a table', 'code', 'practice', 'The book''s Activities 1.2 and 1.3 organize fruit in a list and animal names with their counts in a table. In Jargon, the fruit list is one list, while the table is represented as a list of rows. Run the program and inspect the two structures and their printed data.', 'code', 'SET fruits (["apples", "oranges", "bananas", "kiwis", "mangos"])
SET animals ([["tigers", 6], ["monkeys", 17], ["giraffes", 7], ["meerkats", 23]])
