values ('itf-f-ch4-l4-s1', 'itf-f-ch4-l4', 'itf-f-ch4-l4-milestone', 1, 'Sorting changes list order', 'discussion', 'intro', 'Initially, items in a list are organized in the order in which they are added. Sorting means rearranging data based on a criterion, such as alphabetical order; a sorted list is easier to search. In Example 4.1, the Trip List is in signup order: Donna signed up first, followed by Anna, Harvey, Carl, and Grace. Sorting changes the places of those data items. Names can be sorted alphabetically, while numbers can be sorted by increasing numerical value. The chosen criterion supplies the rule for deciding which item should come before another.', 'text', '', null, '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::jsonb, ARRAY['itf.data.sorting']::text[], 1, 'explanation', null)
