values ('itf-f-ch4-l5-s1', 'itf-f-ch4-l5', 'itf-f-ch4-l5-milestone', 1, 'Queues are first in, first out', 'discussion', 'intro', 'A queue is a type of list. New items are added to the end, while old items are removed from the beginning. Items entering first therefore leave first: first in, first out. In Example 5.1, students who stand in line first return their books or board the bus first, while newcomers join the end. The operating system uses queues to track device tasks in the order received. In Example 5.2, its printer queue contains Section 6A, Section 6B, and Section 6C. It sends Section 6A first, removes that completed task, and then sends Section 6B, which is now at the beginning.', 'text', '', null, '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::jsonb, ARRAY['itf.data.queue', 'jargon.list']::text[], 1, 'explanation', null)
